comment:
Blown away by this Rye. 
Starts off with Carmel and butter
Followed by the oak, char, and ends with a smooth light peppery rye. 
Best rye for the $ of 2020.

This is a solid rye expression, it’s got a sense of rye grain on the palate, with some fresh mint, herbs and oak spice that compliments the bread palate as well. I do think it’s very distinctive from a lot of ryes, in particular ones with the MGP high rye profiles. Unique and really a journey for me.
I would like to know what Woodinville puts in this magical juice. Can’t get enough. Great rye flavor.
On the nose I get allspice and dried Cherry. On the finish I get a little cinnamon and clove. Not long finish but still nice.
whiskey was good. needs more flavor. charlie got this on 01/22.
Lots of sweet dark fruit with some mint, with notes of fennel and baking spice
nice and spicy. a nice wooded sweet note. a good long burn, not too much to kill you, but just enough to let you know it's there.
Smooth finish with hints of caramel

Another favorite. Smells sweet and fruity. After it sits on my tongue for a few moments I find there is a sudden pop of fruit and maple. The flavor is lasting and has notes of light cloves, honey and cinnamon. The aftertaste has a pleasant caramel and apple.
Cinnamon and leathery nose, smooth honey-carmel, oak finish with a solid bite for a 90 proof.  Will be adding this to the rotation for sure.
Interesting and complex rye. Heavy pepper and spice notes. Strong licorice presence. Getting red fruits, even strawberries, on the taste.
Great liquid to learn the difference between “heat” and “spice”. I love this Rye.
I enjoy the flavor, but I find it abrupt. There's a lingering tingle of rye on the palate, but the mouth feel is thin. It isn't very complex, but the flavors present are tasty.
Very impressed with Woodinville Rye! Has a sweet spice start and a smooth lingering finish.
Great body and richness, spicy rye kick. The spices are on the lighter side, like baking spices, but I love the body.
Might as well have peppers distilled, the kick is that strong. I am Smaug!
great simple rye. a nice way to fly. great smell of good rye.
Sweet and a bit sassier than bulleit
